<section id="command-radarctan">
    <title>RADARCTAN</title>
<indexterm><primary>RADARCTAN</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>RADARCTAN</command> <parameter>angle</parameter>
(<command>RADARCTAN</command> <parameter>x</parameter> <parameter>y</parameter>)</synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
With one input, outputs the arctangent angle of <parameter>num</parameter>, in radians.
With two inputs, outputs the arctangent angle of <parameter>y</parameter> / <parameter>x</parameter>, in radians.
See also <link linkend="command-arctan">ARCTAN</link>.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
    <programlisting><userinput>SHOW (RADARCTAN 1) = PI/4</userinput>
true</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</section>
